Here is the commit message:
Fix bug #69720: Null pointer dereference in
 phar_get_fp_offset()

Here is the root cause:
The bug was caused by a null pointer dereference when attempting to access the link source of a Phar entry. If the entry had a link but the link source was not valid (i.e., it was `NULL`), the code would attempt to dereference this null pointer, leading to a crash or undefined behavior.

