The code statements that fix the bug are:
```c
phar_entry_info *link = phar_get_link_source(entry TSRMLS_CC);
if(!link) {
    return FAILURE;
}
(*ret)->zero = phar_get_fp_offset(link TSRMLS_CC);
```
Reason:
The fix introduces a check for the null pointer returned by `phar_get_link_source(entry TSRMLS_CC)`. If the link is null, the function returns `FAILURE` instead of attempting to dereference it, thus preventing the null pointer dereference and ensuring safe execution.

